      },
      "daily_reflection": "So today, I had for breakfast, raspberry and biscoff baked oats. For lunch, I meal prepped chicken and veg stir fry yesterday. So I made a couple of portions. So I had that for my lunch. And then for dinner, I made like a Chinese fake away. So it was, sweet and sour chicken with rice and homemade chips. And a couple of my friends came over and I cooked for all of them. So, it was a nice treat. I suppose does it reflect my typical day to day food habits? It's not completely far removed, but I am actually working from home completely this week. Normally, on Thursdays, I'm in the office. So, like bake making baked oats in the morning, I usually wouldn't unless I'm working from home. It usually be something quicker like overnight oats or I'd have premade like, egg and bacon bagels. But the fact that I was working from home today, I did a little bit more freedom in my, I suppose, and time to cook. And, yeah, I usually wouldn't cook such an extravagant kind of meal with so many components midweek usually. But because I was working from home and because, I was obviously socializing, I went a little bit more all out for my dinner. And my lunch would usually I usually meal prep something, because work is so busy regardless if I'm in the office or in work or in at home. So having that chicken stir fry, even if I was in the office, I'd have brought that with me and just heat it up there. So that didn't really, I suppose, change too much just because I'm at home today. So, yeah."
