      "daily_reflection": "So today, was a back to the office day. So I haven't been in the office in over a week, due to multiple reasons, but it's back to normality this week. So for breakfast this morning, I made baked oats. I've had them kinda prepped last night, and I just popped them in the oven this morning. And that had, there was actually pecans and sunflower seeds. And I actually had two tangerines with it. I just forgot to take a picture of them with it. And then for lunch, I ate in the canteen, because I wasn't prepped enough today to, bring my own lunch, which I normally do. So I got a ham and cheese toastie in the canteen in work. And then for dinner then, I made a homemade Thai red curry, with rice and just a couple of homemade chips. And I ate that at home, and my housemates were there. So while I didn't cook for them, we were all cooking at the same time similarly. So we all kinda ate around the same time. I would say this is a fairly, typical day of eating when I'm in the office. As in I when I came back there, I met that curry, and that'll do me for two or three days. So I'll probably end up having that for dinner tomorrow or bring them for lunch or something. And I usually always end up probably one day out of the three working days that I'm in the office, usually having to get something from the canteen, which is fine. But, yeah, I would say that would kind of as a typical eating day for me, on a Tuesday. So"
